Juneteenth is a day of reflection and renewal. It is a pride-filled day taken to appreciate the African American experience and is inclusive of all races, ethnicities, and nationalities in allyship.
Join us as we reflect on our past and acknowledge the work we still have to do. @meditatewitheve and @wizdomisms lead us in an exercise focused on increasing our ability to listen with our full attention, bringing more mindfulness and kindness to our allyship.

node.title: Mindful Allyship with Eve & Dr. Wizdom Powell

node.text: Who *hasn’t* stayed up late binge-watching the latest @netflix series? This time though, instead of keeping you up with gotta-know-what-happened cliffhangers, this show was created to actually help you fall asleep before the credits roll. Check out Headspace Guide to Sleep, now streaming on @netflix.

Let’s reframe our stress, together. ⁠
⁠
🧡 Pause and reset: before we go any further, take a few deep breaths, in through the nose, out through the mouth.⁠
⁠
🧡 Try to create distance between yourself and the feelings of stress to observe them instead of feeling them. ⁠
⁠
🧡 Zoom out: Step back from the feelings and take in the larger picture.  Seeing the story from a different perspective can help you gain clarity.⁠
⁠
🧡 Show yourself compassion for whatever feelings you may be feeling.⁠
⁠
#FindSomeHeadspace

node.text:
Welcome to Self-Care Sunday! ⁠
⁠
Take back your time and find some headspace.⁠
⁠
Today’s Exercise: Relieve stress with play! Some types of play can actually reduce your stress hormones, cortisol and adrenaline, and trigger the release of endorphins, which can elevate your mood and help you relax.⁠
⁠
Whether that means:⁠
🐶  10 minutes of fetch with your puppy,⁠
✏️ making time for the morning crossword, ⁠
🎾  or plans for a friendly tennis match,⁠
incorporate play into today’s schedule. ⁠
What will you do? Tell us in emojis below. 👇✨

In these past months, we’ve all experienced moments of  uncertainty; steps back, steps forward, fear, excitement, change … just to name a few.  But we can say one thing for certain: it has been a lot. ⁠
⁠
As we step into this world of uncharted territory, we ask you to join us as we stop, sit, and breathe.⁠
⁠
Tune in as we work through change together and focus on ways to approach stress, sleep and anxiety through mindfulness, compassion and self-care. ⁠
⁠
Find your own kind of normal. It all starts with a few deep breaths. ⬆️ #FindSomeHeadspace

node.text: Taking time to connect with nature can have positive effects on our cognitive, emotional, and spiritual well-being, lowering anxiety and stress levels and improving brain function and attention span. You don’t even have to get outside and camp for the full weekend — simply looking out a window or tending to houseplants can have benefits.
